"n.渗透；潜移默化 【英】 n. 渗透(the diffusion of fluids through a membrane or porous partition) 【记】 osm(渗透)+osis→渗 透 【例】 education by osmosis(潜移默化的 教育) n. 渗透; 潜移默化(一种渐进的无意识的同化或吸收的过程) 【记】os通过, m膜, 还是os, is是一渗透作用 【记】音：我嘶摩丝，我湿摩丝→嘶的声音，我在给头发喷摩丝，据说其中的保湿因子能起到渗透头发的作用 osmosis (n.)  1867, Latinized from osmose (1854), shortened from endosmosis (1830s), from endosmose ""inward passage of a fluid through a porous septum"" (1829), from French endo- ""inward"" + Greek osmos ""a thrusting, a pushing,"" from stem of othein ""to push, to thrust,"" from PIE *wedhe- ""to push, strike"" (cognates: Sanskrit vadhati ""pushes, strikes, destroys,"" Avestan vadaya- ""to repulse""). Figurative sense is from 1900. Related: Osmotic (1854, from earlier endosmotic)."
